title: With Wick Back, Saints Start New Season
text:
With Wick Back, Saints Start New Season 
By Zach Schneider October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 9:52 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Things felt normal again on Monday night at Mars Lakeview Arena --- the St. Scholastica men's hockey team was on the ice practicing, and Mark Wick was working in his role as head coach. 
Wick is starting his 12th season in charge of the Saints, back with the team now after missing the last seven games of last year while on personal medical leave. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
What makes being back even better, he said, was the level of excitement he has for this year's team. 
"Like all of our teams, they're going to compete and play hard," he said. "I'm really excited that we have a very veteran group. We have 16 juniors and seniors. In this league, that's what you need." 
One of those veterans is senior goaltender Tyler Bruggeman, who shares Wick's optimism for the year ahead. 
"I think we're going to be really exciting to watch," Bruggeman said. "We're really fast, and we're tenacious on pucks. That's how we've always played."
